'''Hematine''' (also '''magnetic hematite''', '''hemalyke''' or '''hemalike''') is an artificial magnetic material. Hematine is widely used in jewelry. 

Although it is claimed by many that it is made from ground [[hematite]] or [[iron oxide]] mixed with a [[resin]], analysis has demonstrated it to be an entirely artificial compound, a [[Ferrite (magnet)|barium-strontium ferrite]].<ref>[http://www.mindat.org/min-35948.html ''Magnetic Hematite'' on Mindat.org]</ref>

