{{About|the unit of weight|other uses|Kantar (disambiguation)}}

A '''kantar''' is the official [[Culture of Egypt|Egyptian]] weight unit for measuring [[cotton]].  It corresponds to the US hundredweight, and is roughly equal to 99.05 [[Pound (mass)|pounds]], or 45.02 [[kilogram]]s.  It is equal to either 157 kilograms of seed cotton or 50 kilograms of lint cotton.<ref>
