'''Pisit Charnsnoh''', from [[Trang Province]], [[Thailand]], cofounded the ''Yadfon Association'' in 1985. He was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2002, for his efforts on protecting the coastal ecosystems of Thailand.<ref name="goldman">Goldman Environmental Prize: [http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/91 Pisit Charnsnoh] (Retrieved on November 10, 2007)</ref><ref>[http://ecotippingpoints.org/our-stories/indepth/thailand-mangrove-restoration-community-management.html Taking Back the Mangroves with Community Management]</ref> Charnsnoh is on the board of the international Seattle-based [[Mangrove Action Project]], and is affiliated with the ''Industrial Shrimp Action Network''.<ref name="goldman"/>

