{{primary sources|date=July 2015}} {{Infobox film | name = The Messenger | image = | alt = | caption = | film name = | director = Su Rynard | producer = {{unbulleted list|Joanne Jackson|Sally Blake|Diane Woods|Martin de la Fouchardiere}} | writer = Su Rynard | screenplay = | story = | based on = <!-- {{based on |[title of the original work] |[writer of the original work]}} --> | starring = | narrator = | music = | cinematography = | editing = | production companies = {{unbulleted list|SongbirdSOS Productions|Film à Cinq}} | distributor = | released = {{film date |2015|4|28|[[Hot Docs]]}} | runtime = 84 minutes | country = | language = English | budget = | gross = }}
'''''The Messenger''''' is a 2015 [[documentary film]] written and directed by Su Rynard, focusing on the protection of multiple types of [[songbird]]<nowiki/>s throughout the world. The film's world premiere took place at the [[Hot Docs Canadian International Documentary Festival]] on 2015-04-28.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.strictlydocs.com/hdday6/ |title=Hot Docs: DAY 6 – THE MESSENGER |author=Steve Gow |accessdate=2015-10-21 |work=Strictly Docs }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://boxoffice.hotdocs.ca/WebSales/pages/info.aspx?evtinfo=38249~446634ba-e848-4237-9b3c-72aceddb5263&epguid=b314c44a-eed5-4434-9c2c-cc86c0bf61ee |title=The Messenger (programme note) |publisher=Hot Docs Canadian International Documentary Festival |accessdate=2015-10-21 }}</ref><ref>http://songbirdsos.com/the-messenger-world-premiere-at-hot-docs/</ref>
==Cast==
The film features German composer and DJ [[Dominik Eulberg]], expert Dr. Bridget Stutchbury, Michael Mesure, Dr. Christy Morrissey, Turkish ecologist Çağan Şekercioğlu, and ornithologist Alejandra Martinez-Salinas.<ref>http://songbirdsos.com/the-messenger-world-premiere-at-hot-docs/</ref>
==Accolades== At the Hot Docs festival, ''The Messenger'' finished third in the audience balloting.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=Toronto Star |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2015/05/04/us-documentary-unbranded-wins-audience-award-at-hot-docs.html |title=U.S. documentary Unbranded wins audience award at Hot Docs |date=2015-05-04 |author=Linda Barnard |accessdate=2015-10-21}}</ref>
==Release== US Rights for the film were acquired by [[Kino Lorber]], which started a limited theatrical run beginning in December 2015.<ref>{{cite news |work=Variety |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/songbird-documentary-the-messenger-kino-lorber-1201616986/ |author=Dave McNary |date=2015-10-13 |accessdate=2015-10-21 |title=Songbird Documentary ‘The Messenger’ Gets U.S. Release}}</ref>
